SUMMARY:Batik Lampshade Workshop (sign up by 4/24/26) - see full photo bel
 ow
DESCRIPTION:Santa Rosa Creative Circle\n**Brought to you by Batik artist V
 oonbin Pettit**\n\n**Have you ever thought about making your own batik lam
 pshade? Join us for a 5 hour batik lampshade workshop where we’ll teach 
 you everything you need to know to paint a beautiful custom batik lampshad
 e.**\n\n**We'll start with the history of batik and proper use of the tjan
 ting tool to apply wax to define your pattern. Then you’ll learn various
  techniques to add color and bring your beautiful painting to life. Finall
 y\, you’ll learn how to remove the wax and leave with your colorful cust
 om lamp! All materials are provided\, including wax\, tjanting\, fabric dy
 e and lamp. You’ll practice on a 7-inch 100% cotton canvas and your main
  piece will be a 8-inch tall\, 16-inch wide lampshade with LED light and s
 tand\, which you’ll take home - a perfect accent for a desk or reading n
 ook.**\n\n**Schedule:**\n**• 12:00–12:15 PM – Introduction to batik*
 *\n**• 12:15 –12:30 PM – Learning how to use the tjanting**\n**• 1
 2:30–2:00 PM – Waxing (mencanting) your**\n**lampshade design**\n**•
  2:00–3:30 PM – Learning batik coloring techniques**\n**• 3:30–4:3
 0 PM – Remove wax and install batik piece to lampshade frame**\n**• 4:
 30–5:00 PM – Wrapping**\n\n**Sign up Link: https://www.iridescentbatik
 .com/workshops/68**
